@startuml UseCaseDiagram
left to right direction

actor Customer
actor Carrier
actor Manager
actor "Invited User" as InvitedUser

' --- Customer ---
Customer --> (be able to register)
Customer --> (be able to log in)
Customer --> (be able to log out)
Customer --> (be able to recover password)
Customer --> (be able to update personal information)

Customer --> (view list of available products)
Customer --> (search products by name)
Customer --> (filter products by category)
Customer --> (view product details)

Customer --> (be able to add products to the cart)
Customer --> (be able to remove products from the cart)
Customer --> (be able to update product quantities in cart)

Customer --> (be able to place an order)
Customer --> (view order status)

' --- Carrier ---
Carrier --> (view orders ready for pickup)
Carrier --> (mark order as picked up)

' --- Manager ---
Manager --> (be able to add new products)
Manager --> (be able to edit product information)
Manager --> (activate or deactivate products)
Manager --> (manage product categories)
Manager --> (update product stock levels)

Manager --> (filter customer orders)
Manager --> (view sales reports)

' --- Manager invites users ---
Manager --> (be able to register a new manager)
Manager --> (be able to register a new carrier)

(be able to register a new manager) --> (create user account) : <<include>>
(be able to register a new carrier) --> (create user account) : <<include>>

(be able to register a new manager) --> (send invitation email) : <<include>>
(be able to register a new carrier) --> (send invitation email) : <<include>>

InvitedUser --> (complete registration)

(complete registration) --> (set password) : <<include>>
(complete registration) --> (activate account) : <<include>>

' --- System Internal (optional) ---
(be able to place an order) --> (validate product stock)
(be able to place an order) --> (send order confirmation email)

@enduml